In this way, a partial summary of votes, one or more electoral packages will be possible under the following conditions: the electoral results do not agree; there is no record of counting votes and calculating in the relevant field or the chairman does not have it available; or if errors and obvious violations of electoral results have occurred.
In addition, the total recalculation of votes in all electoral posts will be possible if there is an indication that the difference between a potential election winner and a second-place candidate is less or equal to one percentage point; whenever an explicit request from a party representative appears at the beginning of the session and/or a coalition proposed by a candidate in the second place.
The total recalculation may also be carried out if, after proper addition, the difference between the likely winner and candidate in second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, and also whenever there is an explicit request from the political party whose candidate ended in second place, in which case the electoral packages for which a partial summary has been carried out will be eliminated.
